[Student "E"]
{[showcards W:CA N:C4]

You are West. The bidding has been as shown. Partner led the \CA, dummy played the \C4 

Play the \C8 to encourage a continuation. East will play the \CQ on which you will play the \C2.

East now knows you started with a doubleton, and more importantly, he also knows you want him to play a third \C.

When he next plays the \CK dummy will ruff, but whatever card he ruffs with you will have established a trump trick. When you later win your \SK that will be down 1.}
[Play "W"]CA

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:AK5.AKQ5.AT6.QT3 73.J843.KJ952.82 J84.762.84.KJ965 QT962.T9.Q73.A74"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
2C pass 2D pass 2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "606b7c3abe6faffb2e869b885bc8607efde2f07813b56f7655c6b743b36b291a"]
[Category "Defense"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "defense/defensive_signals"]
[Student "W"]
{[showcards S:CQ]

You are South. The bidding has been as shown. You led the \D5, North wins the \DQ and returns the \D7. East holds up his \DA until the third round. He then plays the \CQ  

Play the \C8.

You assume (hope) that North holds the \CA. If he does then he will need help from you to decide which trick he should win. You play the \C8 first, and the \C2 next to show an even number.

If North is paying attention he will know to win the THIRD \C. This will kill dummy's \C suit, and with it East's chance of making 9 tricks.}
[Play "W"]D5

